ACT:
 Indian Penal Code, 1860: Section 304-B (As inserted by Act 43 of 1986)--Scope and object of--Dowry death-Death occuring prior to insertion of Section 304-B Section 304-B held prospective and consequently inapplicable--It contains a substantive provision creating a new offence and, does not merely effect a procedural change for trial of pre-existing substantive offence.
 Indian Evidence Act, 1872: Section 113-B. Presumption as to dowry death--Section 113-B contains rule of evidence to prove the offence of dowry death.
